# MEMORY.md — Index Root

> This file is the single entry point into the memory tree. It lists
> categories and points to their `INDEX.md`; it does not contain memory
> content itself. Keep entries to one line each.
>
> Retrieval tiering: literal/grep match first (free) → local embedding
> search (no LLM token cost) → embedding + reranker (slowest, highest
> precision) only when the first two are ambiguous.
>
> Freshness: memory files in governed categories carry
> `metadata.last-verified: YYYY-MM-DD` in frontmatter; a scheduled gardener
> flags anything older than the configured threshold.
>
> Dual-section rule: governed categories (see list below) store files as
> Current Conclusion + append-only `## History`. Changing a conclusion
> requires appending a history line, not editing history in place.

## 🔥 Most Important Right Now (optional — recency-weighted work only)

- <YYYY-MM-DD> · <one-line pointer to what changed and why it matters> → [slug](category/slug.md)

## Categories

- **user/** — facts about the person(s) this agent serves → [user/INDEX.md](user/INDEX.md)
- **feedback/** — corrections received, generalized into rules → [feedback/INDEX.md](feedback/INDEX.md)
- **projects/** — state of ongoing work → [projects/INDEX.md](projects/INDEX.md)
- **partners/** — facts about third parties this agent interacts with → [partners/INDEX.md](partners/INDEX.md)
- **reference/** — reusable technical/procedural knowledge → [reference/INDEX.md](reference/INDEX.md)
- **lessons/** — distilled, generalizable rules from incidents → [lessons/INDEX.md](lessons/INDEX.md)

Non-governed, freeform areas (not subject to the dual-section rule — mark
your own house rules here if you add any): scratch/working notes, session
logs, secrets/credentials vaults, raw archives.

## Archival

Superseded content moves to a category's `_archive/` subdirectory rather
than being deleted. Leave one line stating why it was archived and what,
if anything, superseded it.
